tps://api.github.com/users/frank-king/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2022-03-15T22:13:36Z", "updated_at": "2022-07-25T14:04:36Z", "closed_at": "2022-07-25T14:04:36Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "<!--\nThank you for filing a bug report! \ud83d\udc1b Please provide a short summary of the bug,\nalong with any information you feel relevant to replicating the bug.\n-->\n\nNothing here is unsound, just surprising. I tried this code:\n\n```rust\nuse std::io::Read;\n\nstruct LieLieLie(bool);\n\nimpl Read for LieLieLie {\n    fn read(&mut self, buf: &mut [u8]) -> std::io::Result<usize> {\n        if core::mem::take(&mut self.0) {\n            // Take my hand and let's end it all\n            Ok(buf.len() + 1)\n        } else {\n            Ok(buf.len())\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let mut buffer = vec![0; 4];\n    let mut reader = LieLieLie(true).take(4);\n    // Primed the `Limit` by lying about the read size.\n    let _ = reader.read(&mut buffer[..]);\n    // Oops, limit is now u64::MAX.\n    reader.read_to_end(&mut buffer);\n}\n```\n\nI expected to see this happen: The wrapping into `Take` ensures that _no more_ than the specified number are appended to the underlying vector. \n\nInstead, this happened: `read_to_end` enters a very long loop, eventually fails to allocate and crashes.\n\n### Meta\n\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\n```\n1.61.0-nightly (2022-03-14 285fa7ecd05dcbfdaf2f)\n```\n\nThe standard library includes this code: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/83460d5e624e9dff72ea8c8f6e79c10af10a3aa1/library/std/src/io/mod.rs#L2561-L2562\n\n```rust\nimpl<T: Read> Read for Take<T> {\n    fn read(&mut self, buf: &mut [u8]) -> Result<usize> {\n// \u2026\n        let n = self.inner.read(&mut buf[..max])?;\n        self.limit -= n as u64;\n```\n\nWhen the `inner: T` is misbehaved then `n` may end up larger than `max`, causing a wrapping subtraction. A remedy may be changing this to a saturating subtraction.\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"frank-king\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/94981/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/94981/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}